    "details": {
      "blurb": "Gray Maiden second; Asmodean conditioner",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "infernal"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 10
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> the Gray Maidens' de facto second — quartermaster at the Ch.2 muster, ex-knight-enforcer of Asmodeus, author of the Maidens' loyalty-conditioning. She resents Sabina's credit and means to replace her. <strong>Boule's bait:</strong> fake 'Korvosan Revolution' ciphers keep the would-be codebreaker ensconced in her quarters (E21) for at least a week — if she cracks them first, she decamps to Castle Korvosa with the emergency cache (reassign it among the castle's third-floor defenders).</p><p><strong>On the alarm</strong> she relocates to the Nursery (E18) — pre-briefing the garrison with her squad-commander plan (Shield Wall, 11 minutes) — and commands the defense beside Zenobia (round 1: her order grants Zenobia an extra action; round 3: Zenobia returns <em>divine power</em>). Her keys open the vault's cells — including Endrin's — <strong>plus a treasury key that matters in Ch.6</strong>.</p><p><strong>Morale:</strong> below ~40 HP she breaks for her quarters' hidden room, locks herself in, grabs the cache, and escapes to Castle Korvosa on <em>dust of disappearance</em> + a <em>potion of gaseous form</em> — re-encountered in Ch.6 at Vavana Dhatri's side.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
